    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Crankcase, Crankshaft, Connecting
        Rods, And Pistons - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Check Piston Pin Clearance
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Check Piston Pin Clearance</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect piston pins for corrosion or wear. Replace as required.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure>
            <graphic filename="../figd04/D0422A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking for Piston Pin Wear</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston pin</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">1-2 inch micrometer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a 1-2 inch micrometer to measure piston pin outside diameter at two locations 90&#176;
                apart. Measure each end of the pin. Record the range of readings. If piston pin wear exceeds
                specifications, replace piston pin.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure>
            <graphic filename="../figd04/D0425A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Measuring Piston Pin Bore Inside Diameter</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a 1-2 inch telescoping gauge and micrometer, measure each piston pin bore inside
                diameter, at two locations 90&#176; apart.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check piston pin clearance, subtract piston pin outside diameter from piston pin bore inside
                diameter measurements. If clearance exceeds specifications, replace piston pin.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
